\chapter{Evaluation}

This chapter covers the evaluation of this active object system. The evaluation is split into three parts. The first part covers the hardware and the basic functionality, which are the robot movement, the sensor data, the computer vision and the general stability. In the second part the quality of the generated maps is investigated. The last part evaluates the search performance, both within single rooms and in larger indoor environments.

Three environments were available to for test runs. Environment 1 is home environment in a small flat consisting of three rooms. Environment 2 is an atypical university environment consisting of some offices and the robotics-lab. Environment 3 is a part of an university floor with rooms of various different room types. A more detailed description of the environments can be found in section \ref{EvalMapping}.

